## PART 2: PROJECT STRUCTURE

### 2.1 — Directory Layout

```
FabricOS/
├── README.md                    # Master context (already exists)
├── PHASE_0_SPEC.context         # This file
├── kernel/                      # The kernel crate
│   ├── Cargo.toml
│   ├── build.rs                 # Build script (linker script processing)
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── main.rs              # Entry point (_start / kmain)
│   │   ├── serial.rs            # Serial port output (COM1, 0x3F8)
│   │   ├── panic.rs             # Panic handler (no_std requires this)
│   │   ├── memory/
│   │   │   ├── mod.rs           # Memory subsystem root
│   │   │   ├── frame.rs         # Physical frame allocator (buddy system)
│   │   │   ├── page_table.rs    # x86_64 4-level page tables
│   │   │   ├── mapper.rs        # Virtual memory mapping API
│   │   │   └── heap.rs          # Kernel heap allocator
│   │   └── ocrb/
│   │       ├── mod.rs           # OCRB test harness
│   │       └── memory_stress.rs # Phase 0 memory stress tests
│   ├── linker.ld                # Linker script (kernel memory layout)
│   └── targets/
│       └── x86_64-fabric.json   # Custom target specification
├── iso_root/                    # Built ISO staging directory
│   ├── boot/
│   │   └── limine/
│   │       └── limine.conf      # Limine bootloader configuration
│   └── EFI/
│       └── BOOT/
│           └── BOOTX64.EFI      # Limine UEFI binary (copied during build)
├── Makefile                     # Build + run commands
└── rust-toolchain.toml          # Pin nightly toolchain
```

### 2.2 — rust-toolchain.toml

```toml
[toolchain]
channel = "nightly"
components = ["rust-src", "llvm-tools-preview"]
```

This pins the project to nightly and ensures components are installed automatically when anyone clones the repo.

### 2.3 — Custom Target: targets/x86_64-fabric.json

```json
{
    "llvm-target": "x86_64-unknown-none",
    "data-layout": "e-m:e-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-i64:64-i128:128-f80:128-n8:16:32:64-S128",
    "arch": "x86_64",
    "target-endian": "little",
    "target-pointer-width": "64",
    "target-c-int-width": "32",
    "os": "none",
    "executables": true,
    "linker-flavor": "ld.lld",
    "linker": "rust-lld",
    "panic-strategy": "abort",
    "disable-redzone": true,
    "features": "-mmx,-sse,-sse2,+soft-float",
    "pre-link-args": {
        "ld.lld": ["-Tkernel/linker.ld"]
    }
}
```

**Why these settings:**
- `panic-strategy: abort` — no unwinding in kernel, just halt
- `disable-redzone: true` — red zone is unsafe in kernel code (interrupts can corrupt it)
- `features: -mmx,-sse,-sse2,+soft-float` — disable SIMD in kernel (we'd need to save/restore SSE state on every interrupt otherwise). We'll enable SSE for userspace later.

### 2.4 — kernel/Cargo.toml

```toml
[package]
name = "fabric-kernel"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"
authors = ["Dshon Smith <admin@obeluslabs.com>"]

[dependencies]
limine = "0.3"              # Limine boot protocol structures
spin = "0.9"                # Spinlock (no_std compatible)
linked_list_allocator = "0.10"  # Heap allocator

[profile.dev]
panic = "abort"

[profile.release]
panic = "abort"
opt-level = 2               # Optimize but keep debuggability
lto = true                  # Link-time optimization
```

### 2.5 — Linker Script: kernel/linker.ld

```ld
ENTRY(_start)

PHDRS {
    text    PT_LOAD;
    rodata  PT_LOAD;
    data    PT_LOAD;
    bss     PT_LOAD;
}

SECTIONS {
    /* Limine loads kernel at higher half */
    . = 0xFFFFFFFF80000000;

    .text : {
        *(.text .text.*)
    } :text

    . = ALIGN(4096);

    .rodata : {
        *(.rodata .rodata.*)
    } :rodata

    . = ALIGN(4096);

    .data : {
        *(.data .data.*)
    } :data

    . = ALIGN(4096);

    .bss : {
        __bss_start = .;
        *(.bss .bss.*)
        *(COMMON)
        __bss_end = .;
    } :bss

    /DISCARD/ : {
        *(.eh_frame)
        *(.note .note.*)
        *(.comment)
    }
}
```

**Key:** Kernel is mapped at `0xFFFFFFFF80000000` (higher half). This is standard — lower half is for userspace later.

### 2.6 — Limine Configuration: iso_root/boot/limine/limine.conf

```
timeout: 0

/Fabric OS
    protocol: limine
    kernel_path: boot():/boot/fabric-kernel
```

### 2.7 — Makefile

```makefile
KERNEL_TARGET := kernel/targets/x86_64-fabric.json
KERNEL_BIN := target/x86_64-fabric/release/fabric-kernel
ISO := fabric-os.iso
LIMINE_DIR := $(HOME)/limine
OVMF := /usr/share/OVMF/OVMF_CODE.fd

.PHONY: all build iso run run-debug clean ocrb

all: run

build:
	cd kernel && cargo build \
		--release \
		--target targets/x86_64-fabric.json \
		-Zbuild-std=core,alloc \
		-Zbuild-std-features=compiler-builtins-mem

iso: build
	# Create ISO directory structure
	mkdir -p iso_root/boot/limine
	mkdir -p iso_root/EFI/BOOT
	# Copy kernel binary
	cp $(KERNEL_BIN) iso_root/boot/fabric-kernel
	# Copy Limine files
	cp $(LIMINE_DIR)/BOOTX64.EFI iso_root/EFI/BOOT/
	cp $(LIMINE_DIR)/limine-bios.sys iso_root/boot/limine/ 2>/dev/null || true
	cp $(LIMINE_DIR)/limine-bios-cd.bin iso_root/boot/limine/ 2>/dev/null || true
	cp $(LIMINE_DIR)/limine-uefi-cd.bin iso_root/boot/limine/ 2>/dev/null || true
	# Create ISO
	xorriso -as mkisofs \
		-b boot/limine/limine-bios-cd.bin \
		-no-emul-boot -boot-load-size 4 -boot-info-table \
		--efi-boot boot/limine/limine-uefi-cd.bin \
		-efi-boot-part --efi-boot-image --protective-msdos-label \
		iso_root -o $(ISO)
	# Install Limine
	$(LIMINE_DIR)/limine bios-install $(ISO) 2>/dev/null || true

run: iso
	qemu-system-x86_64 \
		-bios $(OVMF) \
		-cdrom $(ISO) \
		-serial stdio \
		-m 256M \
		-no-reboot \
		-no-shutdown

run-debug: iso
	qemu-system-x86_64 \
		-bios $(OVMF) \
		-cdrom $(ISO) \
		-serial stdio \
		-m 256M \
		-no-reboot \
		-no-shutdown \
		-s -S

ocrb: iso
	qemu-system-x86_64 \
		-bios $(OVMF) \
		-cdrom $(ISO) \
		-serial stdio \
		-m 256M \
		-no-reboot \
		-no-shutdown \
		-display none

clean:
	cd kernel && cargo clean
	rm -rf iso_root/boot/fabric-kernel
	rm -f $(ISO)
```

**Commands:**
- `make build` — compile the kernel
- `make iso` — build bootable ISO
- `make run` — build + boot in QEMU (serial output to terminal)
- `make run-debug` — boot with GDB server (attach with `gdb -ex "target remote :1234"`)
- `make ocrb` — headless run for automated tests
- `make clean` — clean everything

