## PART 7: IMPLEMENTATION ORDER SUMMARY

```
Step 1: panic.rs + main.rs skeleton          -> `make build` compiles
Step 2: serial.rs (COM1 output)              -> `make run` prints "Hello from Fabric"
Step 3: frame.rs (buddy allocator)           -> Serial shows memory map + alloc tests
Step 4: page_table.rs + mapper.rs (VMM)      -> Serial shows map/translate/unmap tests
Step 5: heap.rs (kernel heap)                -> Vec/Box/String work
Step 6: ocrb/ (stress tests)                 -> ORI score printed, gate pass/fail
```

**Total estimated files:** 10-12 Rust source files, 1 Makefile, 1 linker script, 1 target JSON, 1 Cargo.toml, 1 toolchain TOML, 1 Limine config.

**Total estimated lines of Rust:** 1500-2500 lines.

